Executive Profile
Lawrence S. Peiros  Group Vice President, The Clorox CompanyAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships62--
Background

		Mr. Lawrence S. Peiros, also known as Larry, serves as an Executive Advisor at Gryphon Investors. Mr. Peiros focuses on consumer products and services. He serves as a Group Vice President at The Clorox Company (formerly, Clorox Corp.) and served as its  Chief Operating Officer from April 8, 2011 to April 1, 2013 and its Executive Vice President from January 2007 to April 2013. Mr. Peiros oversaw Clorox's global business, including the Burt's Bees and Green Works brands ... and leads the Clorox's marketing, sales, product supply and research and development functions, as well as its environmental efforts. Mr. Peiros served as the Chief Operating Officer of North America Region of Clorox Company from January 2007 to April 8, 2011 and served as its Executive Vice President of North America Region since January 2007. Mr. Peiros has more than 30 years of operating and marketing experience in the consumer packaged goods industry. He served for 32 years from 1980 to 2012 and held the Chief Operating Officer role from 2007 to 2012. In addition to wielding overall responsibility for Clorox’s businesses, he also oversaw the Marketing, Sales, Research and Development and Product Supply functions, as well as Clorox’s Eco Office. He served as a Treasurer of The American Cleaning Institute (known as The Soap and Detergent Association). He served as Group Vice President of Household Group at The Clorox Company from January 1999 to January 2007 and had overall responsibility for its U.S. Laundry and Home Care, Auto Care and Brita® water-filtration products businesses, as well as Clorox Canada. Mr. Peiros joined Clorox in 1981 as a Brand Assistant and served as its Vice President of Household Products from December 1997 to January 1999, Vice President of Armor All Products from December 1996 to December 1997, Vice President of Food Products from July 1995 to December 1996 and Vice President of Corporate Marketing Services from September 1993 to July 1995. He served as an Assistant Dean of freshmen at Dartmouth College. Mr. Peiros served as an Independent Director of Annie's, Inc., from February 28, 2013 to October 2014. He has been an Independent Director at Ross Stores Inc. since January 24, 2013, Annie's Homegrown, Inc. since February 2013. He has been an Independent Director at Potlatch Corporation since February 2003. He served as a Director of iRobot Corporation since May 25, 2016. He served as a Director of Clorox New Zealand Limited until April 1, 2013. He served as a Director of The American Cleaning Institute and Oakland Zoo. He received Distinguished Service Award in 2013. Mr. Peiros earned a B.A. in English at Dartmouth College in 1977 and a Master's degree in Business Administration at Stanford University in 1981.Read Full Background




